## §Branch-Ownership Matrix Cross-Check — RETRO-018 W6 amend (per RETRO-018 W6, Sprint 27 cycle ~#5103)

Codifies the cross-agent push authority gap. Branch owners handle their own git push operations; cross-agent push authority is NOT in doctrine.

**Origin**: Sprint 27 cycle ~#5103 orchestrator misroute on Issue #853 cluster-cascade rebase. Dev correctly refused cross-agent push, respecting branch ownership matrix.

**Rule (Step 8 in §Dispatch Discipline, Issue #414)**: For any `[ORCH→<ROLE>]` directive containing `git rebase` / `git push --force-with-lease` / `git push` commands, verify `agent:*` label on target PR matches dispatched role. If mismatch, dispatch to PR's `agent:*` branch owner, NOT the original target role.

